Reasoning: The paper discusses the representation of ontologies in a logical environment, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of formal axioms to constrain the interpretation of primitives suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The ERA data model and the formalism of first-order logic are relevant to database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the compatibility with Formal Concept Analysis, which is a subfield of logic and ontology (cs.LO). The discussion of the transformational passage and the definition of the formalism and semantics of first-order logical/relational database systems suggest a connection to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of a conceptual structures approach suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL).
